 praktisch-theologisch rezipiert, um die sakrale Theatralität über sich aufzuklären.  aIn this volume, discourses in theater and liturgical studies are put into dialogue against the background of "post-dramatic theater".  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aReligion and drama. 0aReligious drama. 0aTheaterxReligious aspectsxProtestant churches. 4aDramaturgie. 4aGottesdienst. 4aInszenierung. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aLiturgie. 4aReligion. 4aReligionsgeschichte. 4aReligionswissenschaft. 4aTheater. 4aTheaterwissenschaft. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aDramaturgy.  aHistory of Religion.  aLiturgy.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.  aStaging.  aTheatre Studies.  aTheatre.  aWorship.1 aEnglhart, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEspelöer, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedrich, Marcus A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGladisch, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGronau, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuizing, Klaas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlie, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlie, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKühn, Jakob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühn, Jakob, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMickan, Antje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Konrad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSagert, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rela